net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format

Class SegmentContainerSequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format.Segment
      • net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format.SegmentContainer
        • net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format.SegmentContainerSequence
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SegmentContainerRepeat

    public class SegmentContainerSequence
extends SegmentContainer
    A SegmentContainerSequence is a SegmentContainer that matches if all the contained Segments match the stream in the order of occurrence. It is used to concat smaller Segments to compose bigger parts up to the final format pattern.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
